ere I check if optional features are available with `Diagnostics.isOptionalAvailable()`, plus validating versions. If optional is false due to the classpath, the test passes, but that could lead to coverage misses. I need to tighten things up to true and add an assertion there. It seems this test might only reach line 110 in `validateVersion` and not in `doReport`, so I’ll edit that too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UB7G2afGWdw4FWWSmZyFVjF8|fc_06426b067a42cc6a0169fbb7f1cab0819c959cbf0d2abdd27b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/org/apache/env/DiagnosticsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    void availabilityAndVersionValidationUseOptionalTaskLookup() {\n        boolean firstLookup = Diagnostics.isOptionalAvailable();\n\n        Diagnostics.validateVersion();\n\n        assertThat(Diagnostics.isOptionalAvailable()).isEqualTo(firstLookup);\n    }", "newText": "    void availabilityAndVersionValidationUseOptionalTaskLookup() {\n        assertThat(Diagnostics.isOptionalAvailable()).isTrue();\n\n        Diagnostics.validateVersion();\n\n        assertThat(Diagnostics.isOptionalAvailable()).isTrue();\n    }"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 826, "output": 1470, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51448, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778104282179, "responseId": "resp_06426b067a42cc6a0169fbb7db1470819cab46441e12f94fe6"}}
